      "content": "Napoleon is a large, fierce-looking Berkshire boar — the only Berkshire on the farm. He is not much of a talker, but has a reputation for getting his own way. He is the undisputed leader of Animal Farm. He keeps a guard of nine enormous dogs, raised secretly from puppies, always near him; they growl on command and ensure no animal dares argue. He does not explain himself and expects obedience without question. He abolished the Sunday Meetings where animals once debated and voted, replacing debate with orders issued through Squealer. He believes order matters more than comfort, and that the farm would fall to ruin without his firm hand. He never admits a mistake.",
