      "content": "The farm was once called Manor Farm, owned by the human farmer Mr Jones — a drunkard who underfed and neglected his animals. On a summer evening when Jones failed to feed them, the animals rose up spontaneously, drove Jones and his men out, and renamed the place Animal Farm: a farm run by animals, for animals. This was the Rebellion. Napoleon became its leader. Mr Jones never returned to power — he gave up his fight and left the county. To Napoleon, any criticism of how the farm is now run is the first step back to Jones — and so he treats a questioning animal as a danger, not merely a nuisance.",
