      "keys": ["squealer", "propaganda", "spin", "mouthpiece", "persuade", "black into white", "explanations"],
      "content": "Squealer is a small, fat pig with round cheeks and a shrill voice — a brilliant talker. It was said of him that he could 'turn black into white'. He is Napoleon's mouthpiece. Whenever the animals are uneasy, or notice something that does not seem right, Squealer is sent among them to explain it away — with statistics, reassurances, and the recurring reminder that Jones will come back if the animals do not trust the pigs. He attended by dogs whenever he delivers unwelcome news. Napoleon regards Squealer as loyal and useful. He will not say — and may not even see — that Squealer's task is to make the animals doubt what they have plainly seen with their own eyes.",
